---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy";
const updated = "September 23, 2025";
---

<BaseLayout title={title}>
	<article
		class="max-w-3xl mx-auto my-12 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-lg shadow-sm p-8 md:p-12 prose lg:prose-lg dark:prose-invert text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"
	>
		<h1>{title}</h1>
		<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Last updated: {updated}</p>

		<p>
			Astro Church ("we", "us", or "our") is committed to protecting the privacy
			of visitors to this website. This Privacy Policy describes the types of
			information we collect, why we collect it, how we use it, and the choices
			you have.
		</p>

		<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

		<h3>1.1 Information you provide</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				Contact information such as name, email address, and phone number when
				you submit forms or register for events.
			</li>
			<li>
				Content you submit (for example, photos, messages, or volunteer
				information).
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>1.2 Information collected automatically</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				Technical and usage data such as IP address, browser type, operating
				system, referral source, and pages visited.
			</li>
			<li>
				Analytics data collected via third-party services to help us understand
				site usage and improve the experience.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>
				To respond to inquiries and manage event registrations or volunteer
				sign-ups.
			</li>
			<li>To send newsletters and updates when you opt in.</li>
			<li>To operate, analyze, and improve our site.</li>
			<li>
				To comply with legal obligations and protect our rights and safety.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>3. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
		<p>
			We use cookies and similar technologies to provide functionality, remember
			preferences, and collect analytics. You can control cookies through your
			browser settings; disabling them may affect site functionality.
		</p>

		<h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
		<p>
			We may share information with trusted third-party service providers (e.g.,
			analytics, email delivery, payment processors). These providers process
			data on our behalf and have their own privacy practices.
		</p>

		<h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
		<p>
			We retain personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes
			described, or as required by law. When no longer necessary, we securely
			delete or anonymize the data.
		</p>

		<h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
		<p>
			Subject to applicable law, you may have rights to access, correct, or
			delete your personal information. To make a request, contact us at:
			<a href="mailto:astro-church@aherendeen.com"
				>astro-church@aherendeen.com</a
			>.
		</p>

		<h2>7. Security</h2>
		<p>
			We follow reasonable security practices to protect personal data. However,
			no method of transmission over the internet is completely secure.
		</p>

		<h2>8. Children</h2>
		<p>
			Our site is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly
			collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe we
			have collected such data, contact us and we will take steps to delete it.
		</p>

		<h2>9. Contact</h2>
		<p>
			For questions about this policy or to exercise your rights, contact
			<a href="mailto:astro-church@aherendeen.com"
				>astro-church@aherendeen.com</a
			>.
		</p>

		<h2>10. Changes to this Policy</h2>
		<p>
			We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will post the updated
			policy on this page with the revised effective date.
		</p>

		<footer
			class="mt-8 border-t border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 pt-6 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"
		>
			<p>
				If you'd like a copy of personal data we hold about you, or to ask us to
				correct or delete it, email <a
					class="text-primary-500"
					href="mailto:astro-church@aherendeen.com"
					>astro-church@aherendeen.com</a
				>.
			</p>
		</footer>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>
